<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Well, no..this ALONE would not finish the matter line, but it woudl be a nice addition and certainly help us in many group (and some solo) situations.<P>When you are in an area where you cannot get a pet, this woudl be great.  Higher spec in matter woudl also by default mean more deadly DOTs, which many of thoe other 88% pet classes don't get. Nor our debuffs.<P>So yes, I woudl use the 88% pet. Some people actually spec high matter JUSt for the DOTs, and this would be the extra boost needed to bring their solo power back up. Sure soemthing extra might need to go into matter also, but you have to consider this.<P>As it is, if you go with matter you forgo a pet completely. No isn't a weaker pet you can summon anywhere a bit better than no pet at all?<P>And a side note... Yes Rhia is a Female. This i know for a fact, or i hope for her signifigant others sake.... boy would he be surprised.<P>And as for undead, we were as close to getting charm undead as you can be without ever actually getting it at one point. I never pushed Jim on the point, but he WAS considering it for us, and that consideration may bear fruit soemtime in the future. Do the epic quest and you will see it is not only not far fetched, but woudl follow in the footsteps of MANY mages we all know in our wonderful Albion.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...
