I think the IDEA of a pet sword and shield is cool, but I'm going to have to agree with Battik.  The only think I was excited about when I first read the idea is that the sword/shield can parry/block.  I can see the faces of the archers when they snipe us only to see their arrow bounces off...&lt;evil grin&gt;<P>But truthfully, why would you choose the best pet in the game vs a crappy pet that you can't buff, especially if run-buff is fixed?  Sure it would be nice during certain situations, but it's debatable.  During groups, a lower pet would not help get aggro off you, and a wimpy pet can't help tanking like a strong pet can.  And pets in groups are generally not needed/wanted.  &lt;agree with Battik&gt;<P>Now in rvr was where I thought this new pet idea would really shine, but really it would only be good for the parry/block part.  So why not just make a new defensive spell, Force-Field.  A bubble surrounds the caster where all fast-moving objects have a chance of being pushed away or derailed.  Say an arrow is being shot, the Force-Field might make the arrow whizz pass our head instead of hitting us.  Or a sword that was about to hit true on our chest be instead pushed to land a blow on the arm instead. Fits telekinesis theme imo.<P>--------------------<P>Sephrenia Fairheart<BR>44 Sorceress of Guinevere<BR>34(43)mind/0(5)matter/30(35)body
