<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
How about a damage reducer spell. There are many damage adds such as the the thuergist/wizard and palading chant; this is merely the reverse. It has a damage per second that it subtracts when cast on allies.  Such and effect could be easily explained in the matter/telekenisis line.<P>I think the sorceror (and the cabalist) suffer for not having any ally affecting spells other than the run buff. Sorecerors are the only int casters (in Albion, haven't checked the others) that have zero spells that target an ally (and the Cabalist life transfer is of dubious value). I think this makes the classes less group friendly and worthless if you are a few levels below the group average (because of resists).  This is very different for Thuergist or Clerics, which is part of why they are easier to level.<P>Anyway, if this were baseline, it would help both classes to at least appear more group friendly.  Balance could be done by adjusting the amount of damage it reduces.
</FONT>
