My 2 points on previous ideas:<P>The animate undead thing doesn't sit well with me. From a roleplaying standpoint, I do not want to be an outcast. If you recall your level 15th Academy quest, they are appalled at the practice and "as long as the light of Camelot shines on the Academy" they will not condone Necromancy.<P>The other ideas.. which offer major game changes.. like Teleporting, are also a bad idea... I don't want random people sending me tells asking if I can do something like that.<P>As others have said... new spells need to have more substance than just damage, but they can't be something that noones going to want to spec in Body anymore. That would just reverse the situation we have now. This unfortunatly excludes any kind of defensive spell, in my opinion. Making us another hybrid class that can't do one thing well without gimping their character is a bad plan.
