Like the idea of the animated shield, having a pet with attacks and such just infringes a bit on the Cabalist's identity, however having a shield to block an arrow once in awhile would be a nice thing.<P>One other quick idea I thought of while reading one of i3ullseye's early posts with force pushing enemies off battlements was to have some sort of high range spell to interrupt archers. I don't think having a shield against them is balancing, archers should be able to kill casters easily, however if we're on our toes and quick enough perhaps we could have a force shove spell with good range.<P>So the archer shoots you, you manage to get oriented quickly and quickcast your high range shove (1500 would not cut it for dealing with archers). The archer get's pushed back and is interrupted, you sprint forward for 2 seconds, cast again and try to keep the archer distracted until you can get into mez range. Good archers would be able to time their shots "around" the shoves to get enough off to kill the caster, and good casters should be able to topple lesser skilled archers... as it is now an archer with little skill can kill a very good Sorcerer, which is wrong IMO.<P>Just a thought to help with archers and fit into the telekinesis line.<P>--------------------<P>Polgara the Sorceress<BR>Sorceress of Nimue
