I pretty much agree with Battik here.  The only grounds I would like the animation idea is that a full matter spec sorcerer would also have a pet.  <P>Of course even as it stands now a full matter spec would have speed (basline spell) and a dot with good range and power (the 50 matter dot)so would be very strong, at least in RvR.  Sure they probably would not solo so easily, but then some of us (like me) never solo.  So a full matter spec does not really need a pet IMO<P>I do certainly think matter needs something though. It is one of the worst spell lines in the entire game. One useful spell that only surpasses the baseline choice at very high spec levels? Totally absurd. I orignally thought they would just throw an AE Dot or AE stun into matter to balance it out, but that could have been easily done already, so my guess is they are designing something more interesting along the lines thought here.<P>Personally I hope for<P>1) Projectile reflection field, perhaps even returning them to attacker<P>2) Point blank AE stun/dot.  'Crushing Stun' or something. Makes total sense and adds some much needed variety. Could us that nifty wizard earthen power animation and would have to be used with care since it would draw a fair amount of aggro.  I really love this idea best.<P>3)Dampening field.  A castable buff that would reduce all projectile damage by a percentage based on spec.<P>4) The aforementioned shapechange into equal level monster idea.  Wonderful sounding, but I doubt it will happen.  Does not seem like it would be too difficult to code though. Equal level monsters are almost always weaker than equal level tanks so it would not be overpowering I think.<P>Ellejienne of Percival
